    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>BRAZIL INFLATION DROPS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Jennifer L. Rich</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Rich, Jennifer L</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Brazil's May inflation rate reaches lowest level in 18 months, as prices rise meager 1/100 percent (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Brazil's inflation rate reached its lowest level in 18 months in May -- nearly nothing -- reflecting the impact of high interest rates that kept consumers out of stores. According to the benchmark IPC index, consumer prices rose 0.01 percent in May, compared with an increase of 0.42 percent in April. The economy's inflation rate in the first five months of the year was an annualized 3.4 percent.</p>
        <p>Jennifer L. Rich (NYT)</p>
      </block>
